                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "525PL",
                                  "name": "prdBodyA",
                                  "fill": "#444444",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "content": "## Executive Summary\nBroad experience marketplaces are crowded, but resident-verified itinerary products remain underbuilt. Demand is rising as travelers push back against overtourism and seek more meaningful local context.",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 13,
                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "Tuqzt",
                                  "name": "prdBodyB",
                                  "fill": "#444444",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "content": "## Why Now\nSolo travel is growing, overtourism backlash is real, and travelers increasingly value resident perspective over polished but generic activity catalogs.",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 13,
                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "yy8tj",
                                  "name": "prdBodyC",
                                  "fill": "#444444",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "content": "## Biggest Risk\nThe hard problem is not itinerary generation. It is building enough trusted local supply, proving authenticity, and staying differentiated from large marketplaces with better distribution.",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 13,
                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "AmNIX",
                                  "name": "prdBodyD",
                                  "fill": "#444444",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "content": "## Entry Thesis\nStart with a narrow promise: one excellent solo-traveler itinerary per city, built from verified local picks, then expand depth only after trust and repeat purchase patterns emerge.",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 13,
                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "frame",
                                  "id": "NlL61",
                                  "name": "strategicRecs2",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
