                                  ]
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "nZuM0",
                                  "name": "prdBodyD",
                                  "fill": "#444444",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": "fill_container",
                                  "content": "Business Idea Summary\nCore Concept\nA community-driven travel platform where solo travelers can purchase custom itineraries featuring authentic, local experiences curated by residents rather than tourist attractions.\nProblem Statement\nSolo travelers struggle to discover genuine local experiences and often end up at overcrowded tourist spots. They want authentic cultural immersion but lack access to insider knowledge that locals possess about hidden gems in their cities.\nTarget Audience\nSolo travelers seeking authentic, off-the-beaten-path experiences. Likely millennials and Gen Z who value unique experiences over luxury, are comfortable with technology, and prefer cultural immersion to traditional sightseeing.\nValue Proposition\nAccess to insider local knowledge that guidebooks and mainstream travel apps don't offer. Each itinerary provides genuinely local experiences curated by people who actually live in the destination, creating more meaningful and memorable trips.\nKey Features/Offerings\nCustom itinerary generation based on destination and personal preferences\nCommunity platform where locals can submit and verify hidden gems\nOne-time purchase model for personalized travel plans\nFocus on experiences locals actually enjoy (neighborhood cafes, local markets, community events, etc.)\nBusiness Model\nOne-time itinerary purchases with revenue sharing between the platform and local contributors. Potential for tiered pricing based on itinerary depth and customization level.\nMarket Positioning\nPositioned between generic travel apps and expensive local tour guides - offering authentic insider knowledge at an accessible price point for independent travelers.\nSuccess Metrics\nNumber of destinations covered, community contributor growth, customer satisfaction scores, repeat purchases, and authentic experience ratings.\nAuthenticity Strategy Suggestion: Implement a local verification system where experiences must be endorsed by multiple residents, rotate recommendations to prevent over-tourism, and perhaps limit access to maintain exclusivity.\nFeel free to continue refining your idea or ask any questions!",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 13,
                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                }
                              ]
                            }
                          ]
                        },
